column1: #Text=OntoMathPro: A Hub for Math Linking Open Data (LOD)
#Text=The OntoMathPro ontology has been developed by a [research group](https://github.com/CLLKazan) from Kazan Federal University (Russia).
#Text=This ontology is bilingual (English/Russian) and is geared to be the hub for math knowledge in the Web of Data.
#Text=We shared the sources with the Semantic Web community to engage our colleagues from elsewhere in its further development.
#Text=We are going to create an ecosystem of datasets and mashups around the ontology.
#Text=We use a human readable format [OWL 2 Manchester Notation](http://www.w3.org/TR/owl2-manchester-syntax/).
#Text=Would like to contribute to the ontology or develop your own mashup on it?

#Text=Bringing Math to LOD: A Semantic Publishing Platform Prototype for Scientific Collections in Mathematics // 12th International Semantic Web Conference, Sydney, NSW, Australia, October 21-25, 2013, Proceedings, Part I. - Vol. 8218. - Springer Berlin Heidelberg. - 2013. pp 379-394. #Text=If you leverage the ontology in your research, please cite [2].
#Text='Proceedings of Higher Education Institutions: Mathematics' (PHEIM) dataset is available via [our SPARQL endpoint](http://lobachevskii-dml.ru:8890/sparql).
